INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("308", "1", "2013-02-20 18:47:47", "2013-02-20 18:47:47", "<img class=\"alignleft img-border-3\" alt=\"Steve Johansen\" src=\"http://alwd.org/images/SuzanneRowe.jpg\" width=\"125\" height=\"155\" />The Association of Legal Writing Directors and the Legal Writing Institute announced today that Suzanne Rowe, Director of the Legal Research and Writing Program at the University of Oregon, received the 2012 Thomas F. Blackwell Award, one of the most prestigious awards in the legal writing field.\r\n\r\nProfessor Rowe is a graduate of Columbia University School of Law, where she was a Stone Scholar. She Professor Rowe clerked a federal judge in the Southern District of California and then practiced law as a tax associate in Washington, D.C.Â  Before joining the faculty at Oregon, she taught at the University of San Diego and Florida State University.Â  She was a Luvaas Faculty Fellow from 2008 to 2010 andÂ was named a Dean\'s Distinguished Faculty Fellow in 2010.\r\n\r\nSheÂ is theÂ co-author of five books on legal research is the editor of the State Legal Research Series published by Carolina Academic Press.Â  She has a new book coming out on Federal Legal Research.Â Â She writes a monthly column, The Legal Writer, in theÂ <em>Oregon State Bar Bulletin</em>, which takes a fresh look at writing problems.\r\n\r\n[video type=youtube id=Zn8bJB22YFI hd=false width=\"100%\" height=\"315px\"]\r\n\r\nThe Blackwell Award is given to a legal writing professor who has made âan outstanding contribution to improve the field of legal writingâ by demonstratingÂ  the ability to nurture and motivate students to excellence; creating and integrating new ideas for teaching and motivating legal writing educators and students; and helping other legal writing educators improve their teaching skills or their legal writing programs.\r\n\r\nA joint message from ALWD President Lynn Goering and LWI President Ken Chestek notes that many legal writing professorsÂ are aware of Suzanneâs public service, including as a past member of the ALWD and LWI Boards of Directors, as past chair of the AALS Section on Legal Writing, Reasoning and Research,Â as past ALWD Liaison to the ABA Council,Â as current chair of the ABAâs Communication Skills Committee,Â andÂ as the mastermind of manyÂ informal events to welcome and support new legal writingÂ directors.Â Â But the announcment message from ALWD and LWI notes that it was her behind-the-scenes work that won her the unanimous support for the nomination.\r\n\r\nProfessor Rowe will receive the 2012 Blackwell Award at a reception in Washington D.C. this January during the 2012 annual meeting of the Association of American Law Schools.Â  Suzanne Rowe joins a distinguished list of previous recipients of this award, including Richard Neumann (2003), Pamela Lysaght (2004), Ralph Brill (2005), Mary Beth Beazley (2006), Lou Sirico (2007), Diana Pratt (2008), Linda Edwards (2009), Steve Johansen (2010), and Carol McCrehan Parker (2011).", "The 2012 Thomas F. Blackwell  Memorial Award Recipient", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "291-revision-13", "", "", "2013-02-20 18:47:47", "2013-02-20 18:47:47", "", "291", "http://localhost/alwd.org/291-revision-13/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
