 aware of Suzanneâs public service, including as a past member of the ALWD and LWI Boards of Directors, as past chair of the AALS Section on Legal Writing, Reasoning and Research,Â as past ALWD Liaison to the ABA Council,Â as current chair of the ABAâs Communication Skills Committee,Â andÂ as the mastermind of manyÂ informal events to welcome and support new legal writingÂ directors.Â Â But the announcment message from ALWD and LWI notes that it was her behind-the-scenes work that won her the unanimous support for the nomination.\r\n\r\nProfessor Rowe will receive the 2012 Blackwell Award at a reception in Washington D.C. this January during the 2012 annual meeting of the Association of American Law Schools.Â  Suzanne Rowe joins a distinguished list of previous recipients of this award, including Richard Neumann (2003), Pamela Lysaght (2004), Ralph Brill (2005), Mary Beth Beazley (2006), Lou Sirico (2007), Diana Pratt (2008), Linda Edwards (2009), Steve Johansen (2010), and Carol McCrehan Parker (2011).", "The 2012 Thomas F. Blackwell Memorial Award Recipient", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "291-revision-20", "", "", "2013-02-21 19:32:59", "2013-02-21 19:32:59", "", "291", "http://localhost/alwd.org/291-revision-20/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
