INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("487", "1", "2013-02-21 20:35:19", "2013-02-21 20:35:19", "[caption id=\"attachment_451\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"260\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/edwards-linda1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-451\" alt=\"Linda Edwards\" src=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/edwards-linda1.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"137\" /></a> Judy Stinson, Linda Edwards, and Ruth Anne Robbins.[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe 2009 Thomas F. Blackwell Award for Outstanding Achievement in the Field of Legal Writing was presented to <strong>Linda H. Edwards</strong> by the Association of Legal Writing Directors and the Legal Writing Institute. The award was made by representatives of the two organizations at a reception held in San Diego on January 9, 2009.\r\n\r\nLinda Edwards is the Macon Professor of Law at the Mercer University School of Law and Visiting Professor of Law at the William S. Boyd School of Law at the University of Nevada, Las Vegas. She has taught Legal Writing since 1987 and has long been active on the national scene.\r\n\r\nLinda has served on the Board of Directors of the Legal Writing Institute and the Association of Legal Writing Directors and has chaired the Association of American Law Schools Section on Legal Writing, Reasoning and Research. In 1998, 2000, and 2003, she co-sponsored the Notre Dame Colloquium on Legal Discourse. She has served as a facilitator for the Legal Writing Instituteâs summer Writersâ Workshop. Linda also has been active in many AALS and ABA sections.\r\n\r\nIn addition to writing numerous articles, Linda has authored three books,<em>Legal Writing: Process, Analysis, and Organization, Legal Writing and Analysis,</em>andÂ <em>Estates in Land and Future Interests.</em>Â Her fourth book,Â <em>Briefs That Changed the World: Advanced Strategies in Legal Argument,</em>Â will be published in 2009.", "The 2009 Thomas F. Blackwell Memorial Award Recipient", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "449-revision-7", "", "", "2013-02-21 20:35:19", "2013-02-21 20:35:19", "", "449", "http://localhost/alwd.org/449-revision-7/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("488", "1", "2013-02-21 20:47:19", "2013-02-21 20:47:19", "[caption id=\"attachment_451\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"260\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/edwards-linda1.jpg\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-451 img-border-3\" alt=\"Linda Edwards\" src=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/edwards-linda1.jpg\" width=\"260\" height=\"137\" /></a> Judy Stinson, Linda Edwards, and Ruth Anne Robbins.[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe 2009 Thomas F. Blackwell Award for Outstanding Achievement in the Field of Legal Writing was presented to <strong>Linda H. Edwards</strong> by the Association of Legal Writing Directors and the Legal Writing Institute. The award was made by representatives of the two organizations at a reception held in San Diego on January 9, 2009.\r\n\r\nLinda Edwards is the Macon Professor of Law at the Mercer University School of Law and Visiting Professor of Law at the William S. Boyd School of Law at the University of Nevada, Las Vegas. She has taught Legal Writing since 1987 and has long been active on the national scene.\r\n\r\nLinda has served on the Board of Directors of the Legal Writing Institute and the Association of Legal Writing Directors and has chaired the Association of American Law Schools Section on Legal Writing, Reasoning and Research. In 1998, 2000, and 2003, she co-sponsored the Notre Dame Colloquium on Legal Discourse. She has served as a facilitator for the Legal Writing Instituteâs summer Writersâ Workshop. Linda also has been active in many AALS and ABA sections.\r\n\r\nIn addition to writing numerous articles, Linda has authored three books,<em>Legal Writing: Process, Analysis, and Organization, Legal Writing and Analysis,</em>andÂ <em>Estates in Land and Future Interests.</em>Â Her fourth book,Â <em>Briefs That Changed the World: Advanced Strategies in Legal Argument,</em>Â will be published in 2009.", "The 2009 Thomas F. Blackwell Memorial Award Recipient", "", "inherit", "open", "open", "", "449-revision-8", "", "", "2013-02-21 20:47:19", "2013-02-21 20:47:19", "", "449", "http://localhost/alwd.org/449-revision-8/", "0", "revision", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("489", "1", "2013-02-21 20:49:45", "2013-02-21 20:49:45", "[caption id=\"attachment_484\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"265\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/2003-blackwell-award1.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-484 img-border-2             \" alt=\"2003 Blackwell Award\" src=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/2003-blackwell-award1.jpg\" width=\"265\" height=\"228\" /></a> Lisa Blackwell presenting the award to Richard Neumann[/caption]\r\n\r\nOn January 3, 2003, in Washington, D.C., at the annual meeting of the Association of American Law Schools, the first Thomas F. Blackwell Memorial Award was presented to <strong>Professor Richard Neumann</strong> of Hofstra University School of Law.\r\n\r\nProfessor Neumann was chosen for his outstanding contributions to the improvement of the field of Legal Writing. Among his many contributions are authoring and co-authoring legal writing texts, working to help establish the teaching of legal writing as a respected academic discipline, and counselling innumerable individual teachers over the years.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_485\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"265\"]<a href=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/2003-blackwell-award-b1.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-485 img-border-2     \" alt=\"2003 Blackwell Award\" src=\"http://localhost/alwd.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/02/2003-blackwell-award-b1.jpg\" width=\"265\" height=\"191\" /></a> Amy Sloan, Richard Neumann, Steve Jamar (former President of LWI), Pam Lysaght (former President of ALWD)[/caption]\r\n\r\nThe award was presented by Lisa Blackwell, Professor Blackwell\'s widow, at a reception at the Sea Catch Restaurant in Georgetown.Â Lisa BlackÂ well noted, \"Tom always considered legal writing a crucial component of a sound legal education. I am pleased that ALWD and LWI have decided to honor him by naming their annual award, The Thomas F. BlackwellÂ Memorial Award.\"", "The 2003 Thomas F. Blackwell Memorial Award Recipient", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "blackwell-2003-recipient", "", "", "2013-02-21 21:39:13", "2013-02-21 21:39:13", "", "31", "http://localhost/alwd.org/?page_id=489", "0", "page", "", "0");
